SIMPLE: accompaniment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accompaniment
<hw>Ac*com"pa*ni*ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>accompagnement</ets>.]</ety> <def>That which accompanies; something
that attends as a circumstance, or which is added to give greater
completeness to the principal thing, or by way of ornament, or for the
sake of symmetry.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>A part performed by instruments, accompanying another part or parts
performed by voices; the subordinate part, or parts, accompanying the
voice or a principal instrument; also, the harmony of a figured
bass.</def> <rj><au>P. Cyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accompanist</ent>⟦br⟧
